error: `client_validators:` was never wired to code generation in any released version of reinhardt-web; removing it loses no runtime behavior.

       Migrate to the unified `validators:` block with `#[client(on = submit|input|blur)]` annotations:

           // Before (no longer supported):
           client_validators: {
               username: [ "value.length >= 3" => "Too short" ],
           }

           // After:
           validators: {
               username: [
                   #[client(on = input)]
                   |v| v.len() >= 3 => "Too short",
               ],
           }

       See: docs/migration/0.2.0-client-validators-removal.md

       This custom error is retained through the 0.1.x series. In 0.2.0, the `client_validators` identifier will be removed from the parser and using it will produce a generic `unknown property` error instead.

       Tracked by: kent8192/reinhardt-web#3654
  --> tests/ui/form/fail/client_validators_rejected.rs:17:3
   |
17 |         client_validators: {
   |         ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
